Duties:
 Independently deliver small IT projects to improve IT processes, functionality or performance
 Help improve various ITIL processes within the organisation with documentation, tooling and development of specific solutions
 Develop, test and implement new software programs to support end user and IT requirements
 Test, maintain and recommend software improvements to ensure strong functionality and optimization
 Independently install, customize and integrate commercial software packages
 Respond promptly to incidents, investigate and provide temporary and/or permanent resolution of incidents escalated. Provide timely status updates to relevant parties
 Troubleshoot systems, network and application problems for projects and production issues
 Expected to work during off-peak hours on system activities (e.g. patching, upgrade)
 Provide supporting documentation, reports and other information to management

Required Skills:
 IT engineer with 3-5 years of experience
 Diploma/ Degree in Computer Engineering / Information Technology
 Preferably experience in the financial sector
 Service minded, customer focussed and a good communicator
 Big picture thinking but with attention to detail
 Familiarity with ITIL v3, Agile practices and DevOps methodologies is a plus
 Experience with ITSM systems such as ServiceNow is a plus
 Experience with installation and configuration of database servers such as Microsoft SQL 2008
 Experience developing software utilizing various coding languages including Java and .Net
 Experience with Windows / Powershell scripting
 Experience with IT Security, system hardening, security monitoring
 Experience with Windows Office365 and Microsoft Azure is a plus
 Demonstrated knowledge of web technologies, such as HTML, CSS and Javascript
 Possess up-to-date knowledge of technological developments in the industry
 Outstanding collaboration and communication skills are essential
 Ability to work independently and multi-task effectively